    <stitle>FRONT AXLES: INTERNATIONAL BY SPICER I-BEAM - STEERING KNUCKLE STOP ADJUSTMENT</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="adjust" graphiccount="0">
        <title>STEERING KNUCKLE STOP ADJUSTMENT</title>
        <para>The steering arm stop bolt should be adjusted to permit maximum turning angle. With power steering, the
            stop bolt should be adjusted to assure that the power steering unit will not override the axle stop. Refer
            to GROUP 02 - GENERAL SERVICE INFORMATION AND FRONT WHEEL ALIGNMENT in the CTS-5000 Master Service Manual.
        </para>
    </svcproc>
